{
  "text": "Vibrational Spectroscopy assesses the DC directly by measuring both the percentage of carbon-carbon single bonds in the cured material and the percentage of unreacted carbon-carbon double bonds [CITATION_1] . This is the result of measuring the ratio of absorbance area (intensities) of aliphatic C=C(peak at 1640 cm -1 ) to aromatic C-C(peak at 1610 cm -1 ). The latter is an internal standard before and after composite curing [CITATION_2] . To calculate the DC, the following calculation (formula) is used:",
